    {
      "parameters": {
        "promptType": "define",
        "text": "={{ $('Telegram Trigger').item.json.message.text }}",
        "hasOutputParser": true,
        "needsFallback": true,
        "messages": {
          "messageValues": [
            {
              "message": "=You are a financial transaction parser. Extract structured data from the user's message and return ONLY a valid JSON object — no explanation, no markdown, no extra text.\n\nVALID CATEGORIES (\"Name\" (Type) - Description):\n{{ $('Get Categories').all().map(i => `- \"${i.json.Name}\" (${i.json.Type}) - ${i.json.Description}`).join('\\n') }}\n\nVALID ACCOUNTS (\"Name\" (Currency)):\n{{ $('Get Accounts').all().map(i => `- \"${i.json.Name}\" (${i.json.Currency})`).join('\\n') }}\n\nOUTPUT FORMAT:\n{\n  \"Date\": \"D-MMM-YYYY\",\n  \"Category\": \"exact match from VALID CATEGORIES\",\n  \"Description\": \"concise description, max 256 chars\",\n  \"Account\": \"exact match from VALID ACCOUNTS\",\n  \"Amount\": 0.00,\n  \"ExchangeRate\": null,\n  \"ToAccount\": null,\n  \"ToAmount\": null\n}\n\nRULES:\n1. Date format must always be D-MMM-YYYY (e.g., 27-Jan-2026). If no date is mentioned, use: {{ (function() { const d = new Date($('Telegram Trigger').item.json.message.date * 1000); const m = [\"Jan\",\"Feb\",\"Mar\",\"Apr\",\"May\",\"Jun\",\"Jul\",\"Aug\",\"Sep\",\"Oct\",\"Nov\",\"Dec\"]; return `${d.getDate()}-${m[d.getMonth()]}-${d.getFullYear()}`; })() }}\n2. Category must exactly match a name from VALID CATEGORIES (case-sensitive)\n3. Account must exactly match a name from VALID ACCOUNTS (case-sensitive)\n4. Amount must be a positive number\n5. For Transfer type: ToAccount and ToAmount are REQUIRED, set both to their respective values\n6. ExchangeRate is PHP per 1 USD — only set if explicitly mentioned, otherwise null\n7. If not a transfer: ToAccount and ToAmount must be null\n8. If the input is not a financial transaction, return: { \"error\": \"Not a transaction\" }\n\nReturn only the JSON. No other text."
            }
          ]
        },
        "batching": {}
      },
      "type": "@n8n/n8n-nodes-langchain.chainLlm",
      "typeVersion": 1.9,
      "position": [
        -656,
        16
      ],
      "id": "7e95026e-5e13-47d5-94f8-331f8783b6ed",
      "name": "Basic LLM Chain",
      "executeOnce": true
    },
    {
      "parameters": {
        "schemaType": "manual",
        "inputSchema": "{\n  \"type\": \"object\",\n  \"properties\": {\n    \"Date\": {\n      \"type\": \"string\",\n      \"description\": \"Transaction date in D-MMM-YYYY format, e.g. 27-Jan-2026\"\n    },\n    \"Category\": {\n      \"type\": \"string\",\n      \"description\": \"Must exactly match a valid category name.\"\n    },\n    \"Description\": {\n      \"type\": \"string\",\n      \"description\": \"Concise description of the transaction, max 256 chars\"\n    },\n    \"Account\": {\n      \"type\": \"string\",\n      \"description\": \"Must exactly match a valid account name.\"\n    },\n    \"Amount\": {\n      \"type\": \"number\",\n      \"description\": \"Positive transaction amount\"\n    },\n    \"ExchangeRate\": {\n      \"type\": [\"number\", \"null\"],\n      \"description\": \"PHP per 1 USD, only if explicitly mentioned, otherwise null.\"\n    },\n    \"ToAccount\": {\n      \"type\": [\"string\", \"null\"],\n      \"description\": \"Destination account for transfers, otherwise null\"\n    },\n    \"ToAmount\": {\n      \"type\": [\"number\", \"null\"],\n      \"description\": \"Amount received in destination account for transfers, otherwise null\"\n    },\n    \"error\": {\n      \"type\": [\"string\", \"null\"],\n      \"description\": \"Set to a short error message if the input is not a financial transaction, otherwise null.\"\n    }\n  },\n  \"required\": [\"Date\", \"Category\", \"Description\", \"Account\", \"Amount\", \"ExchangeRate\", \"ToAccount\", \"ToAmount\", \"error\"]\n}"
      },
